Istomin, a magnificent contributor

00:05:50.250 --> 00:05:52.140
to the arts and to music.

00:05:52.140 --> 00:05:55.500
In not only in this country, but
around the world, in the Americas

00:05:55.500 --> 00:05:59.650
and around the world will be
given the Living Legend Award.

00:05:59.650 --> 00:06:04.700
And next spring Mario Vargas
Llosa, I hope you've heard of him,

00:06:04.700 --> 00:06:07.930
Peruvian novelist,
Nobel Prize winner

00:06:07.930 --> 00:06:10.570
who will be receiving
a Living Legend Award

00:06:10.570 --> 00:06:13.240
from the Library of Congress.

00:06:13.240 --> 00:06:17.860
And Dr. Billington has always
had a keen eye for Mexico,

00:06:17.860 --> 00:06:20.670
our neighbor, our closest neighbor.

00:06:20.670 --> 00:06:25.900
In many ways not only our
neighbor but our sibling.

00:06:25.900 --> 00:06:28.960
And someone who is very
much a part of our family.

00:06:28.960 --> 00:06:32.720
So for all of these things,
thank you Dr. Billington.

