00:36:40.360 --> 00:36:44.600
&gt;&gt; Well, I think that we founded
the theatre in the middle --

00:36:44.600 --> 00:36:47.990
very particular time
in Washington D.C.

00:36:47.990 --> 00:36:55.550
Because there were very particular
audience composed of basically,

00:36:55.550 --> 00:36:59.700
I mean, audience, community,
Latino community in Washington,

00:36:59.700 --> 00:37:07.150
who was really conform
of many people immigrants

00:37:07.150 --> 00:37:12.520
from different countries
and their dictatorship.

00:37:12.520 --> 00:37:18.440
So there were people with a very
high grade of education, doctors,

00:37:18.440 --> 00:37:26.510
actors, professionals who had
to leave the country desperately

00:37:26.510 --> 00:37:30.920
to another city and basically
Washington D.C. because many

00:37:30.920 --> 00:37:33.900 position:56%
of them were involved also in trying

00:37:33.900 --> 00:37:37.910
to change what was going
on in Latin America.

00:37:37.910 --> 00:37:44.020
So there was a very particular
audience, very well-educated

00:37:44.020 --> 00:37:49.630
that needed a kind of space
where they could find out,

00:37:49.630 --> 00:37:52.920
where they could enjoy
their own culture.

00:37:52.920 --> 00:37:56.280
And we did plays and
we cannot afford to do

00:37:56.280 --> 00:38:02.320
that because they were very
political, very sociopolitical.

00:38:02.320 --> 00:38:04.110
They were written.

00:38:04.110 --> 00:38:10.890
They were as they say in
the movie place and we broke

00:38:10.890 --> 00:38:16.430
from Latin America, which
has a very European kind

00:38:16.430 --> 00:38:18.550
of literature and theatre.

00:38:18.550 --> 00:38:22.850 position:56%
That never was done in Washington
D.C. I mean, at the time we were one

00:38:22.850 --> 00:38:26.870
of the four most avant-garde
theatres when we started.

00:38:26.870 --> 00:38:28.340
We didn't know that.

00:38:28.340 --> 00:38:35.250
But of course less
the American audience.

00:38:35.250 --> 00:38:43.230
So it is as they say, it is a
question of doing what you need

00:38:43.230 --> 00:38:46.010
to do what your guts tell you.

00:38:46.010 --> 00:38:49.820
And to that people who need it.

00:38:49.820 --> 00:38:53.440
As you said we never thought
about the table or whatever.

00:38:53.440 --> 00:38:56.920
We really wanted to create
this because of the need of it.

00:38:56.920 --> 00:39:01.110
Not only the audience, our
community, but also ourselves,

00:39:01.110 --> 00:39:04.120
this group of artists
from Latin America.

