are losing the Spanish.

00:39:31.390 --> 00:39:33.130
They're not bilingual.

00:39:33.130 --> 00:39:35.880
They don't know, some of them
have never been to the countries

00:39:35.880 --> 00:39:37.770
where there parents came from.

00:39:37.770 --> 00:39:42.590
So looking down the road,
what do you see the future

00:39:42.590 --> 00:39:47.670
of Hispanic theatre is given that
there's this generation of kids

00:39:47.670 --> 00:39:53.430
who don't necessarily have
that emotional and cultural tie

00:39:53.430 --> 00:39:54.830
to language and identity?

00:39:54.830 --> 00:39:57.950
What is the future
shaping up as you look

00:39:57.950 --> 00:40:01.260
at both playwrights
and your audiences?

00:40:01.260 --> 00:40:03.020
&gt;&gt; Tony, you go.

00:40:03.020 --> 00:40:04.610
&gt;&gt; I think it's a brilliant
question.

00:40:04.610 --> 00:40:08.230
I wish I had a way to
look into the crystal ball

00:40:08.230 --> 00:40:09.580
to look into the future.

00:40:09.580 --> 00:40:14.300
But I think that we're dealing
just in you know the amount of time

00:40:14.300 --> 00:40:16.250
that I've been teaching,
which is over 20 years.

00:40:16.250 --> 00:40:20.840
We've see a change in the
way young people think.

00:40:20.840 --> 00:40:25.460
And so to look ten years down
the line or even five years

00:40:25.460 --> 00:40:27.560
down the line with this
technology and the fact

00:40:27.560 --> 00:40:28.860
that they're completely hooked

00:40:28.860 --> 00:40:33.850
to a black screen 24/7
and cannot leave it.

00:40:33.850 --> 00:40:36.280
That's challenge in and of itself.

00:40:36.280 --> 00:40:39.090
Because they are multitaskers
of so many things

00:40:39.090 --> 00:40:41.490
but cannot keep their mind on one.

00:40:41.490 --> 00:40:44.000
And theatre is so much about focus.

00:40:44.000 --> 00:40:45.730
And it's so much about clarity.

00:40:45.730 --> 00:40:47.560
And it's so much about
collaboration.

00:40:47.560 --> 00:40:49.750
It's not so much about this.

00:40:49.750 --> 00:40:53.240
But yet, it's important to
include that because if you don't,

00:40:53.240 --> 00:40:56.710
you start losing that,
your young audience.

00:40:56.710 --> 00:41:02.180
So I think it's a real challenge to
figure out how theatre can continue

00:41:02.180 --> 00:41:05.890
to develop, bring young people
in, and especially Latinos

00:41:05.890 --> 00:41:08.550
so that stories that
they can understand.

00:41:08.550 --> 00:41:11.120
I mean, there's the show right
now called Jane the Virgin

